<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414159>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 8. Leitoscoloplos bifurcatus, A–F: AM W.22967, G, H: AM W.24101. A–E: stereomicroscope, methylene blue staining; F–H: compound microscope.A.Anterior part, lateral view; B.Anterior part, dorsal view; C. Thorax, parapodia of chaetigers 8–13, lateral view; D. Thorax-abdomen transition, lateral view; E. Abdomen, dorsal view; F. Parapodium of chaetiger 37; G. Posterior parapodia; H. Notochaetae (capillary and forked chaetae) of posterior parapodia.Arrows indicate the appearing of the first branchia. a, acicula; br, branchia; cc, crenulated capillaries; fc, forked chaeta; ne, neuropodium; no, notopodium." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4414159/files/figure.png" .

